cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.ET, cs.SE, cs.CY 

This paper is about the design and engineering of ethical reasoners and normative theories for intelligent autonomous systems. It involves the use of formal logic and tool support for experimentation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also heavily relies on higher-order logic, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper deals with ethical and legal considerations, which could place it in cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper's focus on experimentation and case studies could also make it relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
